abstract: Vote for additional witnesses and documents, he implored them, or risk “long lasting and harmful consequences long after this impeachment trial is over.”
snippet: Vote for additional witnesses and documents, he implored them, or risk “long lasting and harmful consequences long after this impeachment trial is over.”
lead_paragraph: Representative Adam B. Schiff of California, the lead House manager, rose one final time on Friday to appeal to a Senate that had already essentially made up its mind against him.
headline_main: With the votes against him, Schiff makes one final appeal for witnesses.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates kicked off a final, frenetic weekend of campaigning ahead of the Iowa caucuses, which will begin the battle to take on President Donald Trump in November.
headline_main: 2020 Candidates Brace for Frenzied, Final Weekend in Iowa
headline_print_headline: 2020 Candidates Brace for Frenzied, Final Weekend in Iowa

abstract: A federal filing showing spending through December provides the most detailed description yet of how Mr. Bloomberg deployed his wealth in a quest for the presidency. The bulk went to advertising.
snippet: A federal filing showing spending through December provides the most detailed description yet of how Mr. Bloomberg deployed his wealth in a quest for the presidency. The bulk went to advertising.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Michael R. Bloomberg put more than $200 million of his personal fortune into his presidential campaign by the end of December, with the overwhelming bulk of that sum going to a mammoth advertising campaign on television and online, according to Mr. Bloomberg’s first campaign finance disclosure with the Federal Election Commission.

abstract: As his impeachment trial moved toward a verdict, some Republicans said they believed President Trump was guilty as charged.
snippet: As his impeachment trial moved toward a verdict, some Republicans said they believed President Trump was guilty as charged.
lead_paragraph: As the Senate marched toward the final phase of President Trump’s impeachment trial, a handful of Republicans coalesced around a common position: Mr. Trump did what he was accused of — pressuring Ukraine to investigate his political rival — but should not be removed for it.
headline_main: Trump did it, some Republicans concede, but should not be removed.

abstract: In a major shift, the Democratic National Committee will eliminate the requirement that candidates to show evidence of grass-roots support.
snippet: In a major shift, the Democratic National Committee will eliminate the requirement that candidates to show evidence of grass-roots support.
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — The Democratic National Committee has opened the door to allowing former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York to participate in the presidential debate it will sponsor in Nevada next month, a change from its practice that demanded candidates demonstrate grass-roots fund-raising support.

abstract: The Trump administration announced Friday that it was restricting immigrants from six additional countries that officials said failed to meet minimum security standards, as part of an election-year push to further clamp down immigration.
snippet: The Trump administration announced Friday that it was restricting immigrants from six additional countries that officials said failed to meet minimum security standards, as part of an election-year push to further clamp down immigration.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration announced Friday that it was restricting immigrants from six additional countries that officials said failed to meet minimum security standards, as part of an election-year push to further clamp down immigration.
headline_main: Trump Curbs Immigrants From 6 Nations in Election-Year Push
headline_print_headline: Trump Curbs Immigrants From 6 Nations in Election-Year Push

abstract: Senator Lamar Alexander described President Trump’s call to Ukraine as “inappropriate.” A reader suggests a more apt word. Also: Hospitality in the Hawkeye State; Australia’s fires; being less digital.

abstract: President Trump’s former chief of staff and secretary of homeland security said the Senate choosing to skip additional witnesses left it with “half a trial.”
snippet: President Trump’s former chief of staff and secretary of homeland security said the Senate choosing to skip additional witnesses left it with “half a trial.”
lead_paragraph: John F. Kelly, President Trump’s former chief of staff and secretary of homeland security, said on Friday that the Senate would be known forever as a body that “shirks its responsibilities” if it wraps up the trial of his former boss without hearing witnesses.

lead_paragraph: The United States has carried out an airstrike against the leader of Al Qaeda’s affiliate in Yemen after months of tracking him by using aerial surveillance and other intelligence, according to three current or former American officials.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
headline_main: Bloomberg Could Qualify for Debates Under New Party Rules
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Could Qualify for Debates Under New Party Rules
